{
  "doc_id": "40731",
  "text": "Fasciola infection induces histopathologic changes where there are parasitic lesions. The histopathologic findings in ectopic fascioliasis are characterized by eosinophilic infiltration and granulomatous lesions formed around eggs and/or worms. Inflammation and fibrosis are seen in the migratory track of the worms. The chronic granulomatous lesion lacks lymphocytes and giant cells [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
